headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero had 29 points and 10 rebounds as the Orlando Magic stormed back from a 21-point first-quarter deficit to beat the Philadelphia 76ers 119-109 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Banchero, Magic rally from early hole, beat 76ers 119-109

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Brooklyn Nets

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving had 26 points, seven rebounds and six assists to lead the Brooklyn Nets to a 121-104 victory Monday night over the Los Angeles Lakers, who played without LeBron James and Anthony Davis.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving has 26, Nets beat Lakers 121-104 as James, Davis sit

headlines.description: — De'Aaron Fox scored 32 points and Trey Lyles had eight of his 11 points in overtime for the Sacramento Kings, who outlasted the Minnesota Timberwolves 118-111 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox, Lyles help Kings outlast Timberwolves 118-111 in OT

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — The defending NBA champions are starting to hit their stride.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry has 38 points, 12 assists as Warriors top Thunder

events.name: Washington Wizards at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Deni Avdija had a career-high 25 points, Bradley Beal had 21 points and the Washington Wizards ended a 22-game losing streak to the Spurs in San Antonio with a 127-106 victory Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wizards end 22-game skid in San Antonio, beat Spurs 127-106

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 53 points in his return to the lineup and Spencer Dinwiddie scored 10 of his 12 in the fourth quarter as the Dallas Mavericks rallied to beat the Detroit Pistons 111-105 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic scores 53 in return, Mavericks beat Pistons 111-105

headlines.description: — Deandre Ayton had to do a double-take in the final minutes as his Phoenix Suns pulled away for another win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges scores 29, Suns pull away late, beat Raptors 114-106

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 42 points, Anfernee Simons hit a tiebreaking 3-pointer with 34 seconds left and the Portland Trail Blazers held off the Atlanta Hawks 129-125 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 42 as Trail Blazers hold off Hawks 129-125
